Third-party notices
===================

This file records attribution for third-party work turbo depends on beyond the
libraries vendored under deps/ that carry their own licence in-tree.


Tree-sitter, and the Elixir and HEEx grammars
---------------------------------------------

Lexilla ships no Elixir or HEEx lexer, so turbo lexes both with tree-sitter
(source/turbo-core/lexers/TSLexer.cxx). Three submodules are vendored and
compiled into the binary:

  deps/tree-sitter            MIT
                              Copyright (c) 2018-2024 Max Brunsfeld
                              https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter

  deps/tree-sitter-elixir     Apache License, Version 2.0
                              Copyright 2021 The Elixir Team
                              https://github.com/elixir-lang/tree-sitter-elixir

  deps/tree-sitter-heex       MIT
                              Copyright (c) 2021 Marlus Saraiva
                              https://github.com/phoenixframework/tree-sitter-heex

  deps/tree-sitter-html       MIT
                              Copyright (c) 2019 Max Brunsfeld
                              https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-html

  deps/tree-sitter-css        MIT
                              Copyright (c) 2018 Max Brunsfeld
                              https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-css

  deps/tree-sitter-javascript MIT
                              Copyright (c) 2017 Max Brunsfeld
                              https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-javascript

Each submodule carries its own LICENSE (and, for tree-sitter-elixir, a NOTICE)
in-tree; those files are the authoritative terms and are distributed with the
source. tree-sitter-elixir is used unmodified.

The grammars' highlight and injection queries (queries/*.scm in each submodule)
are compiled into the binary verbatim: CMake reads them at build time and
generates a translation unit from them, so they remain authoritative in the
submodule rather than being copied into turbo's source. They carry the same
licences as their repositories, above.

Apache-2.0 section 4 requires that this notice be carried in derivative
distributions; the full licence text is at deps/tree-sitter-elixir/LICENSE.

The lexer is validated against the highlight fixtures in tree-sitter-elixir
(test/highlight/*.ex) and tree-sitter-heex (test/highlight/main.heex). Those are
used as a development test corpus and are not distributed with turbo.
